A share is a security that testifies to the contribution of a certain share to an enterprise, which gives its owner the right of ownership and participation in profits.

A share is an instrument for investing capital, it belongs to equity securities. The investment potential of shares depends on a number of characteristics, the main of which are the financial condition of the issuer, reliability, liquidity and profitability.

The investment opportunities of ordinary shares are associated with the fact that they can be traded on the exchange or over-the-counter market and generate income not only in the form of dividends, but also due to changes in value in different periods of time. Fluctuations in value can be very significant and greatly exceed the dividend. Many joint stock companies do not pay dividends, but the value of their shares can increase several times.
